{
  "stem": "14060.8",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Till we-- then we heard that the-- the-- the camp there is going to be vacated by the Americans and taken over by the Russians, so we organized a group of 15 people.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was the youngest amongst them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I looked after the luggage.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We got extra clothing, and, you know, everybody got a bag of something.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we set out from Buchenwald about the middle of June, going back towards Hungary.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it's-- it's-- it's-- it's interesting to note that there are a lot of books written on Buchenwald, because the Americans have well-publicized it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "One of the things which happened was the people under the age of 16, or maybe 17, were taken out of the camp-- those who wanted to.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If they didn't want to, didn't have to-- either to Sweden or to the south of France or to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Whilst these governments have very kindly offered whatever, the Swiss have particularly resisted the numbers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was an American Jewish officer called Lieutenant Berenbaum who was in charge, and there's a whole book written about that where he describes that the Swiss literally didn't want to let in hardly anybody.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they made false-- or printed forms for 400 people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The great Switzerland can take 400 children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when they arrived to Switzerland, the Swiss wanted to turn it back, because they said there are more people than they are prepared to take.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Then the Americans, through the military, has apparently put pressure on the Swiss that they will let it be internationally known.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they are far from white, the Swiss.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then under pressure they allowed the people to come in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I didn't go to neither of these, because I wanted really to know who came back from my family.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
